Bridge from AP stats to higher level stats knowledge

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments:
Strengths - JDRS is a great professor. The videos are great and engaging. Love the virtual format of the class.
Weaknesses - You have to be proactive in staying on top of the content and not allowing it to pile up. Some of the content is not easy. The ULAs were the main weakness of the course - they kept cancelling their office hours and this made it hard to seek help. More stringent rules is required on this front.

Strengths: great that virtual self paced options were created and that slides were provided, quizzes and exam were fairly easy
Weaknesses: need feedback and grades on assignments much earlier because it affects whether we decide to credit D fail

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes if you need it or want a taste of S&DS. It is definitely doable and digestable.
Only if you want a self paced stats option but dont fall behind, would prob recommend another stats class instead where you get feedback more regularly and things are a bit more structured
